dc:description: Mended. Part of A rim modern. Pale orange clay with good glaze; applied white(gone) and red. Reserved: dot concentric circle on underside of foot; foot top; two stripes on lower body. A rim has incised egg pattern between two pairs of incised parallel lines with a white dot in each egg; below, red and white parti-colored band;  pair of incised lines; vine branch(red) originally with white leaves. B: incised egg pattern between two pairs of incised lines, three vertical incised lines hang from the lowest incised line.
